There it is. When any `.webc` file changes, it disables the template cache for that rebuild. Add this to your `eleventy.config.js`:

```js
let internalConfig;
conf.on('eleventy.config', (config) => {
  internalConfig = config;
});
conf.on('eleventy.beforeWatch', (changedFiles) => {
  if (changedFiles.some((f) => f.endsWith('.webc'))) {
    internalConfig.config.useTemplateCache = false;
  }
});
```

Want me to add it?

